docs.lead_paragraph: The Philippine Supreme Court ruled Tuesday that a family planning law is constitutional, allowing the government to provide reproductive health care services primarily to the country's poor despite strong opposition to the law from the Roman Catholic Church.

headline.main: Philippine Court Rules Family Planning Law Legal
headline.print_headline: Philippine Court Rules Family Planning Law Legal
